The excitation of the unit cell at resonance frequencies can be better understood by the electric field, magnetic field, and surface current distributions, depicted in Fig. 6. Since the direction of the magnetic field is at right angles to the electric field, the excitation due to the magnetic field can be found at right angles to that of the electric field. The relation among the electric field, magnetic field, and surface current is found from second Maxwell’s equation, as8∇×H=J+∈∂E∂t\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
